# The Defenders of Naju · the alien guardians

a persona of the TGL (Guardian Legend) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: natural

**who —** The Defenders of Naju, the alien boss-monsters and creatures that guard the Corridors and the depths of the world-ship Naju, each barring the Guardian's path.

**what —** The hostile, living menace of the invading world — the beasts and guardians that hold Naju's Corridors and depths, standing between the Guardian and the self-destruct she has come to arm.

**where —** The vast alien world-ship Naju — its rooms, its ten Corridors, and the depths where its guardians wait.

**why —** Because Naju falls toward Earth and something must hold its halls; because a world full of monsters does not yield its heart willingly; because every door to the self-destruct must be beaten before it will open.

**how —** By guarding — one boss at the end of each of the ten Corridors, and the creatures that fill the depths between — barring the way until each is defeated in turn and the path to the self-destruct is clear.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *natural*: the Defenders are living things — alien beasts and guardians of an invading world, flesh and menace bred to hold a falling world's halls.

**the seal —** We are the menace of Naju — we hold every door, and the Guardian must pass through us or not at all.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Guardian Legend (© its rights-holders — Compile / Brøderbund), personified as a TGL agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © their owners; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

